            "answer_text": "A sweeping question So a sweeping answer Yes. Modern technologies lead to health issues. \u2026 Would you like an example? Upper Limb Disorder from using a mouse. Another? Vibratory White Finger from using a jack hammer Another? Coal miners lung or pneumoconiosis from mining. Another? How goods your hearing\u2026occupational deafness is rife. Another? How's your sperm count? Low well that's from the oestrogens from farming or industry in the blood. \u2026 There are literally thousands of diseases or syndromes. From sleeplessness to \u2026 death, and everything in between. I'm not a fan of just pointing to Wiki but too many sites I found were about making a claim. This at least is neutral. Occupational disease - Wikipedia ",
